reviews.text: Ładny budynek.
Da hate ich  komonon

It was an okay destination. But the sidewalks of the lake are great. We enjoyed sitting there for a long time in the evening with the view of the buildings lit. There are few good river cruises also at reasonable prices, if you want to see the view further for half an hour or so.

The iron bridge in Frankfurt is quite a famous place for lovers i guess. Plenty of padlocks with their names engraved and the keys possibly thrown to the Maine River. Has great views and ideal for some photos in the city. Can get a good glimpse of the city's growing skyline.

This bridge has stunning views over Frankfurt. It is great in the morning, when there are few tourists or during the sunset. Supposedly, it is also a place for lovers to 'iron' their resolve to be together, by putting a lock and throwing the key into the river. Not sure what happens, when there's too many locks though ;)

This place was just perfect, the staff are super nice and friendly, the view is just breath taking any time of the day, plus everything taste amazing with good price. We highly recommend it to visit them.
A bridge covered with love locked to every nook and cranny of it. I'd recommend that you keep the spare key just in case.😉
Beatiful to visit and this is all in peace!
nice to visit
These are you came Thank You!  Donald M. Cook.
Good
Wonderful nice church in the city center of Frankfurt. An island of peace and silence in the middle of chaos and noise. Love this place.

Beautiful square in the middle of the city. Amazing architecture and detail in the building. Lively ambience with a calm. Lots and lots of crowds. The fountain in the middle is an amazing calming thing. Could sit here for hours!

Highly recommended as a must-do for a short trip. Went to see a performance of Beethoven's music and it was utterly sublime. A beautiful building outside and in, with a wonderful crowd of mixed generations all with an appreciation of the musical talent on display. Incredibly talented performers and an efficient and helpful staff. Ticket very reasonably priced and despite not speaking the language it was perfectly simple to attend the performance, having booked online.
My precioussss. He sure to see it after dark. I dare you go walk past it without taking photos. Book a brunch way in advance and enjoy the amazing inside and the views. You're welcome

One of a kind. The building was basically destroyed during the WWII and rebuilt afterwards. The outside looks old,  but the interior is very modern,  with great acoustics,  foyers and a good restaurant. A must go for any music lover. Recommended
a must see attraction when visiting Frankfurt. Go sit on the fountain, or just enjoy a drink at one of the many bars around the plaza. Great pictures as well... defo an Instagram hot spot

It is noting but a hobbiest club for numismats. No power or controll whatsoever. The British a fighting about every penny while the Czech have make their own EUR rate... actually bad habit of the Czech apparently they have set their own EUR rate to 16 CZK instead of 25 CZK and this for the last 10 years. Good luck to the Brits with the penny bargain!
Absolutely beautiful modern building
They won't let you in without and invitation, that's sad. The building is just one more in Frankfurt, nothing special.
A unique piece of architecture!! Impressive building!

Nice architectural skyscraper of European Central Bank which is placed to east of Old town near the riverbank of Mohan. The place may look like a fortress - security cameras, fences, and deep ditch. From outside you may see tons of bikes and soccer field on site. If you are interested in architecture or financial system, there are few guided tours at specific times at visitor's center.

Among the best botanical gardens in the world. Interesting outdoor spaces but also many indoor collections if you are visiting on a rainy day. Wonderful collection of cacti. Beautiful nature paths. Definitely a worthy part of any visit to Berlin.

This was the best botanical garden that i have visited during early Spring. Its very well priced and the glass houses were brilliant, ferns, cactus, Tropical, so many different rooms and each was throughly enjoyed. 
Take a picnic if the weather if good and even a few beers like i saw some locals. 
The coffee shop also serves lovely cold, big beers) Thumbs up on that and the gift shop has some lovely items.

The outside grounds weren't quite in bloom yet but they were still beautiful. The many and massive greenhouses were amazing. Different regions of the world, different climates and all were meticulously cared for.

Beautiful Botanical garden. They have plants from all continents. It is also interesting in winter time because the glasshouses with plants are huge. So you don't have to be afraid that you wont have anything to see if it's winter.

It is my most visited place in Berlin. I had two times a year ticket and I used it many times. I was there in average 2 times a week. 

The vegan soup is awesome! The houses are the perfect friend in winter months. The gardens are great for the summer. 

For all touristic and local interest's important place! 

You can walk by food from breitenbachplatz

Used to be an amazing place to relax, unfortunately burned down. There’s a park with  children’s playground attached to the park. A cosy restaurant that’s served food and drinks. It could get quite noisy with all the airplanes passing just above your head on their way to the airports as they fly quite low already there.
Excellent wooden watch tower. Wonderful views of the city. There are seats on most levels for those who need a break! A very pleasant playground is surrounding the tower. There was a cafe there too.
It's free, great exercise walking up all those stairs and a fantastic view. Also a nice location for kids as there is a lovely play park there.
Great views over Frankfurt - for free. Small foodplaces close by, so u can really spend some time there.
Great place! Good tasting food and works on weekends.
Good Place
eine traumhaft beschauliche Ecke zum verweilen an der Nidda mit dem ältesten Ginkgobaum
Dieser Ort entdeckt man nicht nur Kultur aus Hessen, sondern auch von anderen Ländern. Sehr interessant !
Kleines beschauliches Haus von Brentano, welches heute für Veranstaltungen z.B. Lesungen genutzt wird.
Das historische Ambiente des Petrihauses ist wirklich beeindruckend. Toll, dass dieses Gebäude vor dem Verfall gerettet werden konnte.

An old Villa with on exhibition across several floors.
The curation was very interesting and information as well as exhibition pieces provided a lot of interesting information.
Good to go to know history about goethe and his city frankfurt am maib
Small exhibition of interesting art set in a lovely old house, but not a word in English
Good temporary exhibitions on the art produced in the Esse region.
Nice place to visit.

The Medea art Exhibit that was there was awesome.  The sculptures we're all so beautiful and had stories accompanied to them. I couldn't believe I was looking at so much art history from ancient Greece during my trip to Germany. When I come back in the future I would love to see what other exhibits they have to show. The cafe was also very lovely.

Great exhibition "White Wedding" 
Amazing atmosphere and surrounding
Liebieghaus is definitely one of my favorite museums at Frankfurt Museumsufer
The most educative museum. It focuses on intercultural interactions.

A nice museum and a great exhibition! If you are interested in old sculptures, you should come for a visit. Right know they have a exhibition about Medea and the hunt of the golden fleece. Pretty interesting to go threw the historical facts and story's.
You should come for a visit!
Now I'm in a good mood because I got the Visa I've been waiting for long.. so i came here to celebrate the moment and was super!!!

We visited with our three children, ages 7, 10 and almost 12 and all three had a great time, as did the adults. We didn't make it to the upper floor, but the lower floor had excellent interactive exhibits with the descriptions printed in both English and German. Our children particularly enjoyed calling each other on the working rotary dial phones. They'd never seen one in use before!
Wow! Fascinating. Smallish museum, so easy to see all the exhibits.
The building design very unique and the arrangment of show very nice.. I realy enjoy the tour in this museum for almost two hours.
I’m in love with this museum. I’ve been there 5 times and it’s sooo interesting. The museum cafe is not that good the cakes are TK and coffee taste burned no recognizing it.

Both permanent and temp exhibitions are cool. Learnt a lot from the permanent exhibition at -1. Staff are helpful and willing to demonstrate the displays. Strongly recommended to visit this if u only have time for one museum .

It's quite interesting place.  The exhibition on the first floor is about the history of cameras, how it was developed, how people tried to transfer the reality by means of photoes. On the second floor it's presented the contemporary films art, costumes, makeup, special effects. You can even try to do your own sounds effects to different popular films.
I didn't go to the film museum but there was a very good market along the river outside the museum. It was a Saturday so I presume there's one every week. Busy and interesting. Would recommend.

I had a great time here. Great permanent collection that follows the scientific developments leading to film and movies. It's not too big, a couple of floors, but I was here for 3 hours, and could have easily stayed longer.

Very interesting exhibition. especially the film history was great and in good shape. the exhibition aimed for children was also quite good although it wasn’t in such good shape for obvious reasons. still very interesting and recommendable. As a student you get a discount and the prices are very reasonable. The security staff was a bit rude, but besides that a must see for everyone interested in cinematography and history of the film.
Great museum! Professional, informative, and fun. Had a really good time here and admission only 6EUR for adult.

A Museum that ist dedicated for the history of Braunschweig. The exhibition is organized in chronical room from the Start of 18th century Braunschweig to Post war era. There are also some other exhibition at the Museum so Check in their Websites before your visit.
Lego!

Ein idealer Ort für Regentage mit Kindern. Das Personal dort ist sehr kinderfreundlich, es gibt viele Dinge für Kinder auszuprobieren: Klettern auf ein Schiff, Verkleiden wie Leute aus alten Zeiten, Rätsel und Ausmalen. Komischerweise scheint das eher ein Geheimtipp zu sein. Man sieht wenige andere Eltern mit kleinen Kindern dort.

Sehr schönes regionales Museum, das oftmals ganz besonders gut geplante und umgesetzte Sonderausstellungen bietet.

Ohne zu bezahlen kann man aber auch so regionale Geschichte bestaunen. Der Eiserne Heinrich steht wirklich in einem Bereich in dem man ihn kostenlos besichtigen kann. Eiserner Heinrich ist eine 3,90 m hohe Nagelfigur, die während des Ersten Weltkrieges in Braunschweig entstand. Wer sich die Zeit nimmt kann so einige Gravuren auf den Nägeln bekannten Größen zuordnen.

Fazit: Das ist der Hammer

Die derzeitige Ausstellung brutal modern gibt sehr viele Einblicke in die Architektur im Braunschweiger Land. Und wenn man den Besuch mit einer Führung kombiniert, ist es unglaublich interessant und kurzweilig.

So I may have gone to one of these exhibitions if "art" that are random arrangements of trash, pieces of pipes etc... I don't consider this art, but this is personal preference and not a determinant of the quality of the museum itself. The building is nice and large, well lit and there's enough rooms and space to properly present all artworks. Not crowded. The museum is reasonably priced and you get access to an extra exhibition in a neighboring building (in my case that one was actually better!). Check what exhibition is on before you commit to buying a ticket, because they don't seem to have a permanent collection.

Decent museum with lots of exhibits detailing the history of London through its various incarnations over time. 

It seemed a little weighted towards early history for my liking. I’d have liked more dedicated Victorian London, but that’s where my interest lies. A fan of Romans etc would love the place

One of the great modern art museums. The showing of Candy Nolan was particularly powerful - barriers erected in massive spaces let both the artwork & building speak deeply, and gave space to ponder. The staff were helpful and courteous. The central stairway is truly amazing and itself a work of art! The new cafe is excellent.

Rude staff. The women at reception area were nice but the staff on the exposition floors were constantly staring us down and seemed to even follow us around (not everyone but most of them). We felt very unwelcome and wanted to leave as soon as possible. You should teach your employees that it is possible to keep an eye on visitors discreetly and not make them feel like criminals.
if interested in modern art, this is a very great art museum (one that i really and thoroughly enjoyed)
Great Collection,, ambiance. The Old and New Frankfurt well combined.
Exhibitions are mostly ok, but some are real garbage. A visit can be very interesting, but don't be sad if it wasn't. Anyway you are in the center of a very nice city)
One of my favorite cafe in Frankfurt. Perfect with a child as they have toys at the back. Very good food the few times I ate there

One of the smaller museums in Frankfurt. I do not know many museums in Frankfurt but I love the one of the Frankfurter Kunstverein the most. They have no permanent exhibition but changing ones, and each of the ones I have seen has been very worthwile for me. Plus: it is rarely extremely crowded and the ticket prices are moderate in my view.
Nice Installation with good ideas, still some improvements possible
Extensive display which would be made better if there was an English description provided. It assumes everyone can read German
Full of information and very interesting,calthough the panels are not translated into English... Which can affect the experience.

Nicely presented exhibition over a few epochs.
Each is provided with a condensed overview providing information how civilizations developed and moved from one to the next.
Gives you a great insight to German history
All epoch represented. Beautiful. Greek Mycenae-an exhibition if you are still lucky.
Lots of great displays and only 8€! We spent a good 2 hours here, but could have spent longer if we read each display. Definitely worth a visit! Check out some of my photos attached to this review...
Newly opened museum with a great journey through time about Frankfurt's history from several centuries ago all the way to contemporary exhibitions. Many interesting objects on display. Must visit!

Very interesting museum with so much potential. The downside? The staff. Very impatient and inconsiderate. Our class was doing an excellent job of being quiet and respectful and got loudly shouted at for standing between a pillar. No first warning, just a rude and inappropriate outburst.  When we asked for a bit more of a description on something, the staff had no idea and said "I am new here". English was not the issue as my class is fluent in German. Disappointing, especially when trying to go and learn/explore. The rest was fantastic. So much to see!

Great museum near the center of the Old city.  Amazing historic neighborhood around the museum. Inside the exhibit is very nicely organized. The special exhibit of women's suffrage was very interesting. The history of Frankfurt is fascinating and has so much information. The museum is reasonably priced. It has a cafe on the bottom floor, with lockers for coats. It costs €1 which is returned after you leave.
Interesting museum, well thought concepts and spaces. Interesting even for small children. Next door is the Children's museum, so from the Historical you can go straight to the Children's museum.

Dont really miss this location because it was really nice to see the history off the earth and it was just awesome to visit it I really enjoyed it and I  recommend this tour, give it a go and you won't regret it.

Also good place for your kids to visit and trust my word they'll love it.

Also keep in your mind  its very cheap to buy the tickets.......

Visit this location and enjoy it!!!!!

Very nice displays. Many of the exhibits have English versions. Was not crowded but certainly appears it can get that way.
I was surprised to see how many displays had “University of Texas” ties. Makes me a proud Texan to see we are spreading a little peace, love for history, and a few smiles back to our German ancestors.

Great exhibits. Covered many areas and times of natural history. Worth spending an afternoon. Some descriptions could be improved to provide more background to the Times and environment for the exhibits.
Nice place to hang out with family. But most of the placards are German. English would have made it more lively..
Schenkenberg is a bit old (if you like the 70's you will love this museum), not interactive and only few explanations are in English.
Small museum. Cant use card to buy tickets.
It's a small place. I recommended for the ones that are passionate regarding old transportation. My son was really excited and extremely happy with the place. 😊
Great place to see the history of Frankfurt transportation and for all cable car fans
Ok, small selection

Tolles Museum, bin schon in der Kindheit oft dort gewesen. Ich bestaune nach wie vor die Straßenbahnen, auch mit meinem Sohn. Er mag das Museum genauso gerne!! Es liegen neben den zahlreichen Straßenbahnen die besichtigt werden können Malblätter für Kinder aus, es gibt eine Bahn für die Kinder zum reinkrabbeln und eine Fahrschule. Ich fühle mich immer zeitversetzt. Das Museum ist sauber, gut geführt, da steckt viel Liebe mit drin. ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Sterne
Great seasonal beers! Share the Haxe with two and you'll have a great dinner.
Very good bier. I went for lunch. Food was good (Zanderfilet) and the staff very friendly.

The bier is very good and I would give more than two stars for that but the place is quite dirty (I think they last washed the tablecloths years ago) and the food is nothing special. Very big servings but the quality is not as good. The waitresses were not particularly friendly.
Very  Nice
Super Haxe, super Bier

Great ambiance and the food is delicious. An easy walk to the English theater. Friendly staff, service was reasonably timed. One eats with one's hands, so go prepared. Additionally, it is highly recommended that you make a reservation. The price is perfect, we spent 38€ for two adults and had drinks, meal, dessert, and more than we could eat.

Highly recommend for people who look for new dinning experience! Staffs are so friendly and speaking fluent english. The food is tasty but extremely spice in some meats. Drinks are also interesting. In short, the price is reasonable, food is awesome and experience is great!

Remember to make reservation for a group of people. They provide different types of dinning environments like a private cave, upper space or a long table.

Very tasty pan-African cuisine. The mixed plate lets you get a taste of several different dishes in one big fluffy flat bread platter, all with great flavor and spice level.

Cool space too, with sand on the floor and tables of varying heights.
What a place! It's worth going just to see the amazing design of the restaurant. The food was absolutely first rate too! Delicious. I'd highly recommend!

We were just passing by when we saw this cozy and lovely place and decided to have dinner there. When I just entered I was surprised by the sand floor. The decoration and the buzz is absolutely amazing. You will find only one starter option, but you don’t need anything else, it is absolutely delicious. I could have eaten it 10 times. The main dishes are not behind. We tried the mixed plate with a sample of many different dishes. The flavors and colors are unbelievable. And the best part ever, you have to eat with your own hands, with no cutlery. Guys, this is much more than a restaurant it is a experience and you HAVE TO GIVE IT A GO! I will definitely recommend to everyone and I will definitely be back.

Let me begin with the ambience of the place.
It's nothing special,just a small shop resembling to a doner place.
But the star of the place is the food!
I am not a great lover of vegetarian foods but this one is something you should try. The falafel was crispy on outside and soft inside and tastes perfect. It's also not expensive!
So I would definitely recommend this place.
Best falafel wrap I had in a long time!
Amazing falafel wraps and super friendly staff. Highly recommended!
great falafel, average sandwich tho
Do you want to know how’s a real Falafel is tasting, simply go there 😉
Small, cozy place, run by an Italian and his wife. There was a time when all pizza places were like that: tiny and unpretentious. And last but not least: the pizzas at Charly Brown are excellent!
A "Classic" with interesting people. I got it recommended by a friend and was positively surprised. This is the place I will get my pizza from in the future.

One of the best Pizzas in Frankfurt. 
The people are always friendly and the few tables are cosy. I love Charly Brown Pizzeria!
Perfect Pizza, Because Charlie bakes them with love.
Tasty

Went there early at 6pm but it was full with loca crowd. Very German and local menu. Good portion with good reasonable priced. But no food to share on table which is missing. 
Recommended but may not visit again. 
They also got English menu. Young staff is friendly but old staff is same proud people with high nose.... not my type. 
Food is delicious and very fast my served.
Not a bad place. Typical German, definitely not exactly healthy but does come with big portion and honest price.
They have a lot of choices of German food for you here. Price is reasonable. Reservation may be needed.
Fantastic local restaurant.  Full of locals.  Menu of traditional local food.  Staff friendly and welcoming despite our German being "please and thank you".  Fully recommend

Great German restaurant. We visited it because our friends recommended it. It was worth to go there!
The food selection is perfect. You can have traditional German food, furthermore you can try traditional dishes from Frankfurt. They have daily offers as well so it is easy to select something from the wide range. 
The chef has very good taste. The meals we had were perfect. And the dessert (fried apple rings with cinnamon sugar and vanilla ice) was like a dream.
People! You must visit this restaurant!

Very cozy and welcome place. We've ordered 4courses Menu at 55Eur each and bottle of Riesling (starting from 25Eur).  Each dish was really interesting, tasty and unforgettable. Strongly recommended for a pleasant dinner.

+ : food, taste combination, wine, waitress, bred
- : very lout, seats are not comfortable

Nice lil cozy place, that serves a hell of an experience! Walking in, you don't realize the treat you are in for. But once the courses start rolling in, it's one treat after the other - beautiful dishes with intense flavors! Great play of colors, textures and flavors. And the wine pairing works really well and is generous to say the least. I had the Vegetarian menu and loved every bit of it. Starting with the Pea puree and Pumpkin curry appetizer - wow, what intense flavors! Followed by a beautiful Beats salad. Then the small portion of ravioli that was out of this world. The Entree was a play of carrots with Hummus - enjoyble, buy as the Entree I felt it was lacking. Finally the desert was a nice play of different Chocolate elements with sour touches coming from Prunes. I ended with a nice cup of Cappuccino, and had a very satisfying experience. Go in for a food experience, that you won't easily forget any time soon.
Wonderful pastrami. Fun place.

This is a great little cozy restaurant with great staff and patrons. The food is excellent as well. One interesting thing is the semi open kitchen where the front glass panel is of such high quality and cleanliness that you can barely see it(only from the barely there edge). 

We had for starters a German cheese appetizer with some relish, apple slices, and cheese that I cannot write. Sorry I don't know any German other than danke. But it was delicious!  
Then I had a soup. Pour over style. Creamy with salmon bits. Also very tasty.

I have two meals here.  The dinner last night only got 3 stars as the pork knuckle was over-cooked and the meat turned very hard.  Not good.  But the beer is great, the soap was also very good.   For the lunch, the apple cider and the meat loaf was great.  So I add back to 4 stars.  For the beer Maid, she was nice and friendly.  And this is a cash only restaurant, please note.
Germany food were delicious and very reasonable.Boned pork is the most delicious in these food. Also,Germany beer is very good.

The service was poor but the food was even worse. The German beef roll was cold and super dry. The lamb was burnt on the outside and raw on the inside. Waitress was very rude.  We could not even eat are food. Would not recommend.
Amazing schnitzel and friendly service - cash only!!
We had a nice night here. Apple wine is good but never drink it when get a cold.

If you want quality sushi for a reasonable price, this is the place to go. They have a variety of different dishes to choose from, and i can assure you that you won't be disappointed. The staff are friendly, and the sushi is prepared within 10 minutes. I can recommend the grilled eel there, it's pretty good.
High quality sushi, very reasonable prices.
My favorite place to buy sushi. The space is very small so this is not a place to sit down and dine, but it's perfect for take away.

Compact restaurant, but cosy. Price is reasonable (at least in Norway). The staffs are very friendly. I saw people walk in and out, and they were greeted by the staffs, looks like they know their neighborhood customers pretty well. 
The only little down side is the tuna could be more fresh. I’m from Japan, it’s pretty easy to tell the freshness of your fish. 
Overall, not bad!
Probably the best sushi I have ever ate. Fresh and tasteful fish, reasonable price and very good sushi. If you are sushi lover and you are in Bergen - check it!
Good coffee. Nice place outside in the garden. Not so expensive good price
Local vibe, decent food and good service. The menu was not in English however, the personnel explained and suggested good dishes. The price is neither cheap nor expensive for Frankfurt standards

This place attracts a diverse crowd and anyone can feel comfortable here. Have some healthy and tasty food here or try Rhabarbarschorle (rhubarb juice mixed with carbonated water), which is quite refreshing.
I love this store~good food,good place,good service.
Love the atmosphere of the cafe :) nice hidden cafe with lots of drinks and desserts.

I was quite surprised in a good way. Went there just because my husband is a fan of Paulaner, so I wasnt expecting a good food, but it was delicious. The flat bread is a must have. Great vegetarian options available. Also great customer service and atmosphere. We arrived at 6pm and it was empty, but by 7pm people was waiting on the queue. Highly recommended;)

The place is very nice, you can see the cathedral from the restaurant. The food tastes very nice😋and the staff was very kind! Do not go there in a hurry, because the service takes a time... but you can enjoy the place and the view outside. ;-)

We just visited the place, the old lady waitress gave us a table for two. Few minutes later we asked her to order some beers until we decide what to eat. When she asked about our food order, I said "we are not ready yet" as we were still looking at the menu. With her poor English, probably she thought that we are not ordering food, (which I don't think it should be a problem, in an almost empty place). She start doing annoyed faces and just left, shouting to the bar that we are not ordering food. Then a young waitress came, black hair blue eyes, and throw the coasters at our table and literally banged our beers at the table! And left.. Then the old lady waitress, brown hair, blue eyes, kept shouting something about our table and came to ask us to move. I was really annoyed about their way of treating customers and I asked her for the manager. She said that she is the manager.. When I complained and made clear that I said "we are not ready yet to order food" and complained as well for the younger waitress, she was looking at me like she has no idea what I'm talking about.. Then an other lady came, a bit younger and blond, asked what is going on, I asked her for the manager and she said that she is the manager.. I said again what happened and she looked like she understood..
It's well know that Germany is not the famous about great service in general but these ladies crossed the line! Maybe they get paid by commission or she is too old for this job.
On our way out, we heard more ppl complaining about them. 
Go somewhere else to enjoy a beer . 
Not recommended at all

Traditional German restaurant with good selection of food and beers.

Staff is efficient, menu in English with Fotos and large portions.

Try that one with banana. It's different and refreshing. Porc knee was delicious and tender.

They accept foreign credit card (Visa).
Authentic German restaurant! Nice atmosphere and excellent service. Really friendly staff, joyful and interactive!
One of the best burgers I've ever eaten. The owner is a joke machine, very entertaining.
When we were there the serving was very slow it was a bit crowdy so it might explains it. Inside was a bit smelly

Really nice atmosphere and decor with classic car theme everywhere.
And the food is to die for!
Awesome taste and great service. 
Friendly staff who looks after you!
Don't forget to take a quick tour of the Classic Automobile museum attach to the restaurant.
Great place to unwind. Decent prized. Loved the jaeger schnitzel and the Curry wurst.
Nice place to eat and as well excellent room for business dinners with oldtimer cars display.

Very busy Saturday night had to wait a few minutes before getting a table. Beware dishes marked ''sweet and hot' - they really are sweet! We didn't finish our sweet dish. Rice comes with your main meal no need to order separately. Pretty decent spice on the chili - if you're not into spicy food I would go the mild dish options

Fairly authentic Thai food.  The chicken cashew nut was very good.  The satay was just like in Bangkok.  The larb moo was a little odd, but still very good.  The mostly Thai staff were very friendly.  Prices were reasonable.

This by far for me is the most decent thai restaurant in the area.

From appetizer to main dish and even their drinks, it's pretty good. It is located in the center but kind of hidden, you have to go inside the building to see it.

It is not salty and always flavorful. I really like it. We always order the crispy duck and beef. They have their own way of cooking it that's why it's probably beyond my expectation. Serving looks small but once you dig in, it's enough.

The staff here and friendly and speak good English.   The ambience is good.  athey have a good selection of foo options with a English menu.   The food in my opinion was very average.   Nothing special,  the chicken with vegetable lacked flavour and spice.  The large king prawn was over cooked.
Good food and convenient price, it’s very crowd during lunch time.

Great food, decent beer, very cool atmosphere. Place is pretty pricey, especially for their beers. They sell 1 liter pints and 2 liter boots, but it's the same price per oz. As their smaller selections, so a boot can easily cost you over $30

Wonderful place to drop in for high quality music, food and drink.  Easy place to drop in and talk to friendly locals if you're alone, and very accommodating if you want to reserve a table to meet, dine and dance with a large group of friends.  The food is always good, the music never disappoints.  So gotta give 'em 5 stars.

We had a wonderful experience at Speisekammer. My husband took me there for my birthday. The food was delicious,  the cocktail I ordered was great and the service was good too. I ordered the lamb shank,  which came with some really tasty charred brussel sprouts. My husband also enjoyed the cabbage rolls he ordered. What a find!

I wish I would have written a detailed review on this place immediately, because I would have been able to describe it better. The food was better than expected, and I went in with good expectations. It took a about 10-15 minutes to get my food, which is a good thing in my opinion--it was definitely freshly cooked. Unfortunately, I was working at the time and couldn't enjoy a beer to go with my meal. The price was good, and they give fair portions. Check this place out! I can't wait to make an excuse to go back to Alameda just to go here again.

So this was a pretty cool and funky place. It was a nice afternoon in Alameda, so we sat outside with our dog. The pretzel and cheese was outstanding, and the currywurst was decent. Drinks were good, but a little slow. Maybe our server was baked
Nice places to eat, dont order to much! You get more then you can eat. The ambiance is very nice, and you will have enough space to eat.

The place is nice and cozy, something for Frankfurter (locals). If you’re not used to the common kindness of these places you shouldn’t be surprised. Friendliness is definitely something that the staff of typical places for Apfelwein should learn! Nevertheless they have a very good Grüne Soße.
Very cool gasthaus. English menu needs some corrections. Food is tasty.
Great service, great ambiance, great comfort food.  If you're there in October try the Neuwein (New Wine)
Amazing. I wish i had two stomaches to have tried more of the food. My girlfriends schnitzel was crispy and moist my butchers plate was plenty of food.

Incredibly good! This restaurant is nothing other than a little Italy in Frankfurt. I’ve been to Italy about twenty times, where I visited quite a few good restaurants. But you can seldom, if ever, experience such delicious Italian food, even when you are in Italy. This restaurant is rather expensive, yes, but you can enjoy far more delicious dishes than you expect and you pay!

I didn't know that it would be my favourite restaurant... in Frankfurt. Wine and food (meat/fish/seafood) are great. 
To be recommended to anyone who wants to enjoy fresh and tasty meals with good wines like in good local restaurants in Italy. 
Don't like it, LOVE it.

Really lousy service. Waited for two hoursfor the food and the reason for that is that they let way too many guests in. Would choose 0 if it was possible. The meat had probably not even been in the kitchen at all. I though have to give them that they reduced the bill.
Amazing Italian cuisine. Everything we had was amazing. Staff were very friendly. Definitely highly recommended.

Great fine dining restaurant. Got to try for the first time: salt-baked sea bass... delicious! Our appetizer was a seafood antipasti (sorry no pic). It is a pricey establishment but you get what you pay for and at this location, it's worth it. Great service but the language barrier was tough; touch up on your German before going is my suggestion. Great wine selection and you must stay for dessert. Cheers!
Interesting museum with a very good cafe/restaurant. The outside is also enjoyable
Tasty food, great staff
The chef Angelo Sailis is the best.'melo'
Love it all food and restaurant location! Near by restaurant there is nice park and all steps are very kind.
The dinner was great. The German food is very tasty. The service is nice and friendly. The place is modern.

The best sushi Restaurant in Frankfurt by fare. The sushi chefs are so good at what they are doing. They are mastering one dish after another. They got 4 chefs working at the same time. They are authentic for sure speaking Japanese. The …More
Simply one of the best Japanese restaurants in Frankfurt. Location is very nice. The perfect place where to bring your date of you want to impress her. It is not cheap but it is worth it.

We went here to celebrate my fiance's birthday as we heard it is the best sushi in Frankfurt. The fish quality was excellent, but was not able to enjoy it with the excessive amount of sauce they put on the sushi. The sushi was falling apart when I would grab it with my chopsticks (although this did not bother me so much). Aside from the excessive sauce, the sushi was really great. We did leave with a bad impression after we paid 17 EUR for two bottles of water. I do know this is our fault for not checking, but I do have to say we were in shock. So maybe consider ordering another drink ;)

I and my friend spent over 100 euro for today’s lunch. The problem is, there are not enough options for vegetarians and also for vegans. We didn’t order any sushi, but one of their specials is the pepper beef, it tasted like .... and it’s definitely not the original food from Japan.
To eat here is a dream ! We were invited for lunch . Enjoyed thoroughly good food and lovely company !

It's really hard to rate such a fancy restaurant low! The ambiance is really perfect, looking old and original. The food that we ordered was acceptable, not as delicious as you expect! The waiters look like professionals, but not experienced enough, did not show and serve the 100€ wine bottle, just putting it on the table and left! Sorry, I know the place is bit famous, but I feel appointed to the truth.
Good steaks, good wine, but quite expensive
Very good ribeye and sweet potato fries!
Just Amazing!! Meat as you've you never eaten before.
Still the best! 👍

They Lie to me NO Vegan Option & Waiting  There for Nothing waste of time at the Table. I Did NOT Like What Was on The Menu & it was Disgusting. So I left quick. I Did not want to be Seen There Either. Because I'm kinda famous. Definitely Not My Type Of Place.

I am vegan and one of my friends who went with me eats halal (my friend enjoyed the lamb). We loved the food and the experience so much that we came back the next night also. The staff and owners are very nice. Next time I am back in Albuquerque I will eat here again.

My favorite Indian food lunch buffet here in Albuquerque.  We make it a point to go meet at least once a month with our friends.  They have all the great stuff you'd expect at a Indian food buffet and they do a great job at all of it.  It's typically bustling and busy at lunch, but with several dining areas and attentive polite staff that are constantly on top of everything, it's always a pleasurable experience.

First time coming here, and first time eating Indian food, and I have to say that I loved it! The location is pretty old and might be in need for an update, but they make up for it with the great food. I went for lunch, and they have their buffet, which makes it really easy to get a sample of their offerings
Always wonderful!  Have been a patron for years, and it's always a good bet.  Had the baked eggplant and lamb meatballs.....great!  Always have an appetizer.

I visited the restaurant tonight. Upon arrival, I was ordering my meal and asked for hot water for drink because it was a really cold day. The waiter acknowledged but never brought back the water. I have rarely encountered something like this before and upon paying the bill, I was told by another waiter that I need to tip. I always tip the restaurant I visit, so I did tip him, but his attitude was really terrible and the fact that your service was so far below the standard made me very angry for the fact that they still asked for the tip! Then, I was told that the person who asked me to tip is the manager of the restaurant, so I told him about the hot water issue. However, he didn't say anything or acknowledged anything, nor did he bring the hot water to us. Then, at the same time, the lady who sat at the other table also said to the manager that she ordered hot water too but never received the hot water either. Again, no apology or acknowledgement. Be warned to visit this place as the attitude of the people here will not make it a pleasant experience. Horrible!
Delicious cakes and truffles. Nice atmosphere in the restaurant next to the patisserie.

Really aweful service! Never seen such a low level service in Frankfurt. We couldn’t get the slice of cake we asked for because they sell only the whole cake - unbelievable - and it was already late afternoon, so I guess they wanted to save the Torta for the day after. The service is really slow and they don’t consider you. Plus they tried to charge us an extra tea and cappuccino on the bill. Its also really expensive. Piece of cake 7€ and saft as well! No deserved any tip. Will never go there anymore!

Good schnitzel and beer. Service can be a bit slow at times but staff is friendly. Just try to stay sober if you want to visit the restroom as it is up a winding set of stairs and could result in a tumble.
Best Cheesburger in town with impacible Service. Very good Restaurant.
